sentences: Zachry Alexander Brown (born on July 31, 1978 in Atlanta, Georgia) is an American singer-songwriter, musician, and co-founder and lead singer of the countryâ€“rock Zac Brown Band, as well as electronic dance music group Sir Rosevelt.
In 2019, Brown released a pop surprise album titled The Controversy.

In his mid-teens, Brown spent almost a year being tutored by a vocal coach from his church in Cumming.
He was also a camp counselor at Camp Mikell in Toccoa, Georgia, and Camp Glisson, a United Methodist summer camp and retreat center located in Dahlonega.
In 2017, Brown made an investment into the Stillhouse Creek Distillery in Lumpkin County, Georgia, which was later rebranded the Z. Brown Distillery.
The distillery closed down on November 18, 2018.
Brown appeared in a 2016 episode of Treehouse Masters on Animal Planet.
In 2019, Brown appeared on the Lil Dicky charity single "Earth".
In 2016, Brown was involved in an early morning drug bust at the Four Seasons Hotels and Resorts in Palm Beach, Florida.
